# Implementation Plan: Enhancements & Fixes

This plan outlines the changes to elevate the homepage's premium feel, fix the product filtering logic, update the mobile navbar, remove the delivery checker, and address the newly identified product modal errors (currency encoding and layout).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Filter Logic Change:** The current filter logic enforces "global single-selection" (you can only select *one* filter across the entire sidebar). The plan is to remove this restriction, enabling **multi-selection** (e.g., selecting "English" AND "Class 1" AND "Story Books" simultaneously). 
> 
> **Navbar Search Replacement:** On the homepage (`index.html`) mobile view, the magnifying glass search icon will be replaced with a "Shop" icon linking directly to `products.html`. On `products.html`, the search icon will remain so users can still search.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Product Info Pop-Up Fixes (Encoding & Layout)
Address the layout bug where "Add to Cart" appears in the wrong place and the currency symbol renders as `â,¹`.

#### [MODIFY] [script.js](file:///d:/Projects/mindfuels-master/script.js)
- Fix the currency symbol encoding by replacing the corrupted `',1'` string with the standard Unicode Indian Rupee symbol (`\u20B9`).
- Delete the `<div class="pincode-checker">` block from the dynamic HTML template string used to render the modal.
- Remove the `window.checkPincode` function and its associated logic.

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///d:/Projects/mindfuels-master/index.html)
- Sync the modal HTML structure with `products.html` by wrapping `#modalCartActions` in `<div class="modal-actions-bar">`. This ensures the sticky "Add to Cart" CSS styling applies correctly on mobile, preventing layout breakages.
- Delete the `<div class="pincode-checker">` block.

#### [MODIFY] [products.html](file:///d:/Projects/mindfuels-master/products.html)
- Delete the `<div class="pincode-checker">` block.

